    "Details": "The fourth and most popular model with Wolf warriors is a heat-friendly brawler prepared for any battlefield contingency. This variant retains the left-arm mounted ATM-9 of the original, mounting a large pulse laser in each torso, supported by a pair of ER medium lasers, and two anti-personnel Gauss rifles in its right arm. Three tons of ATM reloads and one of Gauss reloads give the Tundra Wolf 4 impressive endurance.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Easy to Maintain</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.17</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Lower, Right Lower</color>",
